SERRATIA MARCESCENS - VENEZUELA: (CARABOBO) NICU, FATAL REQUEST FOR INFORMATION
*******************************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

[1]
Date: Fri 13 Apr 2012
Source: Globovision [in Spanish, trans. & summ., Mod.JG, edited]
http://globovision.com/news.php?nid=226223


On Friday [13 Apr 2012], relatives of the fatal victims and a member of Carabobo House of Representatives, Mr Miguel Velasquez, appeared before the Public Prosecutor's Office to introduce a formal complaint supported by medical and laboratory records, with respect to the death of 119 newborns in Valencia Central Hospital [AKA Dr Enrique Tejera Hospital Complex].

One little girl died last Saturday [7 Apr 2012]. Her grandmother reported she had written confirmation that the 7-month, pre-term baby was infected with _Serratia marcescens_, which led to cardio-respiratory arrest and eventual death.

Another mother was admitted to Valencia Central Hospital at week 40 of pregnancy. Her baby boy, who had a congenital cardiopathy, died in the Neonatal Intensive Care Unit (NICU) of the bacterial infection.

Another woman declared that her baby was infected with _Klebsiella pneumoniae_. She showed the report from the microbiology laboratory. The baby died 8 days ago.

Relatives of the deceased children expect that investigations will be carried out as fast as possible. They say that this complaint will never bring their babies back to life, but it may prevent the occurrence of similar cases in the future.

--
